verbose_text: ORs showed that individuals with initial serum albumin levels below 3.0 g/dL had a significant increase in the risk of developing simultaneous mediastinitis (2.96), necrotizing fasciitis (10.67), disease extent of more than one cervical level (2.18), and initial serum CRP over 20 mg/dL (4.20) (all P < 0.05) (XREF_TABLE).
